    {
      "id": "el_4",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 65,
      "y": 100,
      "width": 524,
      "height": 22,
      "text": "Basic Profit & Loss Formulas",
      "fontSize": 17,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 17,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 400,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 4,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f0"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Basic Profit & Loss Formulas",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_5",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 65,
      "y": 125,
      "width": 305,
      "height": 281,
      "text": "Profit = SP - CP  (when SP > CP)\nLoss = CP - SP  (when CP > SP)\n\nProfit% = (Profit / CP) × 100\nLoss% = (Loss / CP) × 100\n\nSP = CP × (100 + P%) / 100\nSP = CP × (100 - L%) / 100\n\nCP = SP × 100 / (100 + P%)\nCP = SP × 100 / (100 - L%)\n\nWHY: P% is profit as fraction of CP.\n  SP = CP + P% of CP = CP×(100+P%)/100.\n  Invert to get CP from SP.\n\nEx: CP=400, P%=25\n  SP=400×125/100=500, Profit=100",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 500,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 5,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f0"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Profit = SP - CP  (when SP > CP)\nLoss = CP - SP  (when CP > SP)\n\nProfit% = (Profit / CP) × 100\nLoss% = (Loss / CP) × 100\n\nSP = CP × (100 + P%) / 100\nSP = CP × (100 - L%) / 100\n\nCP = SP × 100 / (100 + P%)\nCP = SP × 100 / (100 - L%)\n\nWHY: P% is profit as fraction of CP.\n  SP = CP + P% of CP = CP×(100+P%)/100.\n  Invert to get CP from SP.\n\nEx: CP=400, P%=25\n  SP=400×125/100=500, Profit=100",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
