    {
      "id": "el_7",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 535,
      "y": 100,
      "width": 599,
      "height": 22,
      "text": "Discount & Marked Price Formulas",
      "fontSize": 17,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 17,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 700,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 7,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Discount & Marked Price Formulas",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_8",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 535,
      "y": 125,
      "width": 328,
      "height": 281,
      "text": "Discount = MP - SP\nDiscount% = (Discount / MP) × 100\n\nSP = MP × (100 - D%) / 100\n\nMarkup m%, Discount d%:\n  SP = CP × (100+m)/100 × (100-d)/100\n  Net P% = [(100+m)(100-d)/100] - 100\n\nSuccessive discounts d1%, d2%:\n  Single = d1 + d2 - (d1×d2)/100 %\n\nWHY: MP is inflated CP. Discount cuts MP.\n  Two steps: CP→MP (markup), MP→SP (disc).\n  Net effect combines both multipliers.\n\nEx: CP=200, m=50%, d=20%\n  MP=300, SP=300×80/100=240, P%=20%",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 800,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 8,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Discount = MP - SP\nDiscount% = (Discount / MP) × 100\n\nSP = MP × (100 - D%) / 100\n\nMarkup m%, Discount d%:\n  SP = CP × (100+m)/100 × (100-d)/100\n  Net P% = [(100+m)(100-d)/100] - 100\n\nSuccessive discounts d1%, d2%:\n  Single = d1 + d2 - (d1×d2)/100 %\n\nWHY: MP is inflated CP. Discount cuts MP.\n  Two steps: CP→MP (markup), MP→SP (disc).\n  Net effect combines both multipliers.\n\nEx: CP=200, m=50%, d=20%\n  MP=300, SP=300×80/100=240, P%=20%",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
